2/1/18 late entry: Similar to Bolleana. Seems to be pure alba. Perhaps a bit wider. Vigorous, healthy, no bld in 1992. Light flowering, pollinate early. Rooting: 1992=65% 17/26 8" cuttings.

2/1/18 late entry: Selected in nursery for vigor in 1992. Flowered @ age 4. Very narrow fastigate tree that is suseptible to BLD, short lived. Ortet rooted 100% but was dissapointing since. Rooting: 1992=100%, 2003=38% (20/53), 2004=32% (19/60).

2/1/18 late entry: Selected in nursery for vigor in 1992. Flowered @ age 4. Very narrow fastigate tree that is suseptible to BLD, short lived. Ortet rooted 100% but was dissapointing since. Rooting: 1992=100%, 2003=38% (20/53), 2004=32% (19/60).
2/1/18 late entry: Excellent form and vigor. Some BLD. Seems to have aspen branching features. 37" circ, 11.8" diameter on 12/26/04. BLD score: 8/28/01=1 Rooting: 2004=0% (0/40)
2/1/18 late entry: Excellent form and vigor. Form is better than aa4101. Seems to have aspen branching features. 37" circ, 11.8" diameter on 12/26/04. BLD score: 8/28/01=0 Rooting: 2004=10% (4/40)
2/1/18 late entry: Used as a control clone. Has a reputation for good, stable performance even on dry sites. Rooting 6" cuttings: 2004=86% (153/178).
2/1/18 late entry: A vigorous tree, fair to poor form. Rooting: 2004=0% (0/20)
